Allied Sets September Shareholder Vote for Transatlantic Deal

-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 
2011-08-19T21:18:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-19/allied-sets-september-shareholder-vote-for-transatlantic-deal.html
Allied World Assurance Company
Holdings AG set a Sept. 20 meeting for its shareholders to vote
on the company’s proposed merger with reinsurer  Transatlantic
Holdings Inc. (TRH)   The meeting will be held in Zug, Switzerland, Allied said
in a regulatory filing today.  Validus Holdings Ltd. (VR)  has made a
hostile offer for New York-based Transatlantic and urged Allied
shareholders to vote against the agreement.  Warren Buffett ’s
 Berkshire Hathaway Inc. (BRK/A)  has also bid for Transatlantic.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Noah Buhayar in New York at 
 nbuhayar@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  